verbose_text: Among the integrin members, the alpha v beta 3 integrin, which binds to arginine-glycine-aspartic acid (RGD)-containing components of the interstitial matrix such as vitronectin, fibronectin and thrombospondin, is expressed in a number of tumor types such as melanoma, late stage glioblastoma, ovarian, breast, and prostate cancer XREF_BIBR.
